<% content_for(:title) { "Privacy Policy" } %>
<% content_for(:description) { "How #{app_name} collects, uses, and protects your data." } %>

<div class="min-h-screen bg-background text-foreground">
  <header class="border-b border-border">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6 py-4 flex items-center justify-between">
      <a href="/" class="flex items-center gap-2 group">
        <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-primary group-hover:scale-110 transition-transform" aria-hidden="true" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path d="M12 2C12 2 8 6 8 10C8 12.21 9.79 14 12 14C14.21 14 16 12.21 16 10C16 6 12 2 12 2Z"/><path d="M12 14V22"/><path d="M8 18H16"/></svg>
        <span class="font-bold text-foreground"><%= app_name %></span>
      </a>
      <%= render UI::ButtonComponent.new(as: :link, href: "/auth?tab=signup", variant: :primary) { "Get Started Free" } %>
    </div>
  </header>

  <main class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6 py-16">
    <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold mb-2">Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p class="text-muted-foreground text-sm mb-4">Last updated: March 17, 2026</p>

    <div class="mb-12">
      <%= render UI::AlertComponent.new(variant: :warning, title: "Template notice") do %>
        This is a starting template. Replace all <code class="bg-warning/20 px-1 rounded">YOUR_*</code> placeholders with your actual company information before going live.
      <% end %>
    </div>

    <div class="space-y-10">
      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-3">1. Who We Are</h2>
        <p class="text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed">YOUR_COMPANY (&ldquo;we,&rdquo; &ldquo;us,&rdquo; or &ldquo;our&rdquo;) operates YOUR_DOMAIN (the &ldquo;Service&rdquo;). This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, disclose, and protect information about you.</p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-3">2. Data We Collect</h2>
        <p class="text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed mb-3">We collect information you provide directly:</p>
        <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-muted-foreground space-y-1.5 leading-relaxed">
          <li><strong>Account data:</strong> email address, name, and password hash when you register.</li>
          <li><strong>Payment data:</strong> billing information processed securely via Stripe. We do not store full card numbers.</li>
          <li><strong>Usage data:</strong> pages visited, features used, and interaction patterns to improve the Service.</li>
          <li><strong>Device data:</strong> IP address, browser type, operating system, and device identifiers.</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-3">3. How We Use Data</h2>
        <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-muted-foreground space-y-1.5 leading-relaxed">
          <li>Provide, maintain, and improve the Service.</li>
          <li>Process transactions and send related information.</li>
          <li>Send transactional emails (verification, password resets, billing receipts).</li>
          <li>Monitor and analyze usage trends to improve user experience.</li>
          <li>Detect, prevent, and address technical issues and fraud.</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-3">4. Cookies</h2>
        <p class="text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed">We use essential cookies for authentication and session management. We may use analytics cookies to understand how users interact with the Service. You can control cookie settings through your browser.</p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-3">5. Third-Party Services</h2>
        <p class="text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed">We may share data with trusted third parties that help us operate the Service:</p>
        <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-muted-foreground space-y-1.5 leading-relaxed mt-3">
          <li><strong>Stripe</strong> &mdash; payment processing</li>
          <li><strong>Email provider</strong> &mdash; transactional email delivery</li>
          <li><strong>Analytics</strong> &mdash; anonymous usage analytics</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-3">6. Your Rights</h2>
        <p class="text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed">You have the right to access, correct, or delete your personal data. You can export your data from the Settings page. To delete your account, use the &ldquo;Delete Account&rdquo; option in Settings or contact us at YOUR_EMAIL.</p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-3">7. Data Retention</h2>
        <p class="text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed">We retain your data for as long as your account is active. When you delete your account, we permanently remove your personal data within 30 days, except where we are required to retain it by law.</p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-3">8. Security</h2>
        <p class="text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed">We implement industry-standard security measures including encryption in transit (TLS), hashed passwords, and regular security audits. No method of transmission is 100% secure, but we strive to protect your data.</p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-3">9. Contact</h2>
        <p class="text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed">If you have questions about this Privacy Policy, contact us at <a href="mailto:YOUR_EMAIL" class="text-primary hover:underline">YOUR_EMAIL</a>.</p>
      </section>
    </div>
  </main>
</div>
